{"/service/ndnp/nvln/batch_nvln_deeth_ver01/data/sn86076356/00332890414/1908030501/0796.xml":{"full_text":"CHICAGO, March 2\u2014Chief of Po\nlice Hhippy was stabbed twice in the\narm and his driver, James Foley, shot\nand fatally wounded by a man who was\nkilled by the chief, in an attacK at the\nHhippy uome tnis morning. Harry\nShippey. son of the chief was shot in\nthe breast when he answered the door\nbell, ami has a fair chaneft of ro\ncovery, acording to the doctors.. The\nbullet passed completely? through his\nbody, just above the heart. The\nwould-be assassin was identified to\nri iglit as a man named l^i/.arus Aver\nbuch. who for the past three weeks\nhas lived at 2JJi Washbur avenpo, on\nthe west side of the city, lps identi\nfication was established thr< ugh tin*\nsister of tin* man, who was fak'e'ri 'by\nthe police tie tlia undertaking rooms,\nAverbuch wna J years obi and oc\ncupied room* with his. sister at the\nabove address. He was a Russlap 'Stu\ndent. He came to America three\nmonths ago from Austria, to which\ncoffritry he fled two years ago, follow\ning the massacre of J-ews in KiaftinefT,\nRussia, where his home had been pre\nviously. His plan to kill Chief Shippy j\nis believed to have been fronted as\ndiroot result; of tlje fatter\u2019* yiterfer\nence with the' parade of the; 'itrietntdoy-\\\ntd men through the city'e *1 rapts sjsv-'l\nyal weeks ago. AveftHieb hits been\nemployed reeetly by a produce corn\nmission firm. .1 j\nX t\nLETTER LIST.\n\nList of.lnUr.ra tcuiwwug\nin the W inn e twice a postotfic.' for toe\nweek ending February 2ft, IftoX\nGeorge .\\Hainan. \u201e,.Laj;g. G. W\nHrvant, C. IilWrMlfe. ,1. 0.\nhtlin, J. Pedrovanejja. mmi.\nOuisRewda. M. I'ffndnll. M O.\nHolden, II. Salmi, Mr.\nHour, Fred. Smith. Fred.\nWeatherford, Mr.\nThese letter\u2019s will be sent to the dead\nletter ufti.ee, March 14. IttOM, if not de\nliered before. In railing for the above\nplease \u00aby aJverT^T^-fclV\u2019intf\u2019'TTaTl'\nof list.\nJ A. ROGER